573
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:02,090
So you've been planning this for a long time, Sir.

574
00:40:02,630 --> 00:40:03,780
Since you've come today,

575
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:04,780
I'm sure

576
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,690
you have plenty to say.

577
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:09,650
Of course.

578
00:40:10,550 --> 00:40:12,100
Today I came

579
00:40:12,350 --> 00:40:13,890
to ask just one thing:

580
00:40:14,150 --> 00:40:15,840
Without the full support

581
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:18,390
of the Ling clan and me,

582
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:20,170
what right or ability did you have

583
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:22,150
to sit securely on the throne?

584
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:23,690
So,

585
00:40:24,180 --> 00:40:25,930
you want to take it for yourself?

586
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:29,610
I have no wish to usurp you.

587
00:40:29,730 --> 00:40:33,160
But I have already received an imperial edict.

588
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:35,940
It states His Majesty is gravely ill with a cold illness,

589
00:40:36,710 --> 00:40:37,750
and thus

590
00:40:37,890 --> 00:40:41,900
he has passed the throne to the prince in the Empress's womb.

591
00:40:42,070 --> 00:40:44,110
He orders me to bear the imperial seal,

592
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:45,910
ascend to the Taiji Hall,

593
00:40:45,910 --> 00:40:47,380
assist the new emperor,

594
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,170
share in handling state affairs,

595
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,960
and oversee the realm and armies.

596
00:40:51,030 --> 00:40:51,820
This minister

597
00:40:52,230 --> 00:40:53,430
dares not refuse.

598
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,940
Why didn't I know

599
00:40:57,190 --> 00:40:58,390
about this edict?

600
00:40:59,230 --> 00:41:00,660
Because...

601
00:41:01,190 --> 00:41:03,090
during today's court session,

602
00:41:03,290 --> 00:41:04,960
you will suddenly be taken ill

603
00:41:05,450 --> 00:41:07,530
and die.

604
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:28,860
You're that sure

605
00:41:29,230 --> 00:41:30,860
everything will go your way today?

606
00:41:32,630 --> 00:41:35,130
The hearts of men are with me.

607
00:41:52,630 --> 00:41:53,420
Good.

608
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:55,610
Very good.

609
00:42:26,750 --> 00:42:27,680
So,

610
00:42:27,950 --> 00:42:29,380
you'd planned ahead all along.

611
00:42:29,990 --> 00:42:31,190
I've already spent the night

612
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:33,330
replacing the Imperial Guards with my own men.

613
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,860
In fact, I could've taken down

614
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,740
the Capital Patrol commander earlier.

615
00:42:38,110 --> 00:42:38,940
But...

616
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,090
I wanted to see

617
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:43,170
just how many people in this court

618
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:44,900
truly stand

619
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:46,420
on your side.

620
00:42:58,670 --> 00:43:01,490
Now that you've seen it for yourself,

621
00:43:02,670 --> 00:43:04,190
allow me

622
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:07,050
to send Your Majesty on your way.

623
00:43:28,340 --> 00:43:33,180
♪Who walks lone through storm and snow♪

624
00:43:34,020 --> 00:43:37,180
♪Reading every warmth and chill♪

625
00:43:38,140 --> 00:43:40,940
♪Of the heart?♪

626
00:43:42,900 --> 00:43:47,100
♪Who stands proud against a thousand weights♪

627
00:43:47,860 --> 00:43:51,300
♪Grace only a mask he wears?♪

628
00:43:51,540 --> 00:43:54,620
♪My blade sweeps the heavens♪

629
00:43:55,540 --> 00:43:58,060
♪Blood once drenched♪

630
00:43:58,820 --> 00:44:01,540
♪My armor and charging steed♪

631
00:44:02,220 --> 00:44:04,420
♪I know what it means to let go♪

632
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:08,740
♪When to step in, when to hold back♪

633
00:44:09,180 --> 00:44:12,300
♪A broken blade cuts through♪

634
00:44:12,700 --> 00:44:15,460
♪Years of winter and summer♪

635
00:44:16,340 --> 00:44:18,380
♪Enemy flags burn to ash like gauze♪

636
00:44:19,220 --> 00:44:24,420
♪Yet my heart still bears the scars of rise and fall♪

637
00:44:24,580 --> 00:44:30,540
♪I'm willing to wield my sword with you and burn the waning moon♪

638
00:44:31,820 --> 00:44:37,700
♪I'm willing to brave all storms with you, boiling with passion♪

639
00:44:38,500 --> 00:44:44,660
♪I'm willing to break my wings and become the blade in your hand♪

640
00:44:45,460 --> 00:44:51,660
♪I'm willing to write with you this torn, enduring page of history♪

641
00:44:52,580 --> 00:44:58,380
♪I'm willing to travel thousands of miles, seeking your ambition♪

642
00:44:59,620 --> 00:45:05,580
♪I'm willing to give my life to keep you safe for a lifetime♪

643
00:45:06,420 --> 00:45:12,940
♪I'm willing to sing through every farewell and wait for you another thousand years♪

644
00:45:13,380 --> 00:45:20,820
♪I'm willing to live and die with you, my one and only wish in this lifetime♪

